 THE National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has begun the training of 100 unemployed women in spice production, processing and packaging in Lokoja, Kogi State. The NDE Director-General, Dr Nasiru Arugungu said that the four-day programme, which kicked off on Monday, under its Women Employment programme, is to create jobs for unemployed Nigerians, in fulfilment of the mandate of the directorate and desire of President Muhammadu Buhari. The Kogi State Coordinator of NDE, Zakari Abubakar enjoined the trainees to avail themselves of the opportunity, noting that it can improve their living standard and “even make them great entrepreneurs.”  